[OVERLAY] VimFu — gV — Avoid Reselect
[SAY] G shift V is used in mappings to prevent the previous visual area from being reselected. It's a mapping helper, not a standalone command.
[SAY] When you run a colon command from visual mode, Vim can auto-reselect the visual area. G shift V prevents that. Let's see the difference.
[SAY] Select three lines.
[KEYS] '2GV2j'
[OVERLAY] 2GV2j  select 3 lines

              1         2         3         
    0123456789012345678901234567890123456789
    ────────────────────────────────────────
