[SAY] Done. Now if a mapping were to reselect here, G shift V would prevent it. It clears the pending visual selection inside a mapping.
[SAY] This is mainly useful when writing custom mappings that execute colon commands on visual selections. You add G shift V at the end of the mapping to prevent re-highlighting.
[SAY] G shift V. A mapping tool to suppress visual reselection. Niche, but handy for clean custom visual mode mappings.